# Arrow Functions

Use arrow functions as the default for function definitions.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ function declaration
function isValidLetter(letter: string): boolean {
  return !!letter && /^[A-Za-z]$/.test(letter)
}

export async function fetchData(): Promise<void> {
  await doSomething()
}

// ✅ arrow function
const isValidLetter = (letter: string): boolean =>
  !!letter && /^[A-Za-z]$/.test(letter)

export const fetchData = async (): Promise<void> => {
  await doSomething()
}
```

## Guidelines

- Use `const name = (args) =>` for functions
- Prefer expression form (`=> value`) when the body is a single return
- Use block form (`=> { ... }`) for multi-statement bodies
- Apply to both regular functions and exported functions
